{"word":"H4117 - מָהַר - mâhar - maw-har' - Endow","slug":"H4117","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מָהַר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>mâhar"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>maw-har'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Endow"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05D4;&#x05E8; - ma&#x0302;har</b> - <i>maw-har'</i><p/>A primitive root (perhaps rather the same as <a href=\"#/H4116\">H4116</a> through the idea of <i>readiness</i> in assent); to <i>bargain</i> (for a wife), that is, to <i>wed: - </i>endow, X surely."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4116\">H4116</a>, <a href=\"#/H4119\">H4119</a>"}]}